headline: Vanguard Settles Texas Lawsuit Alleging Investors Conspired to Drive Up Coal Prices
summary: Vanguard Group agreed to pay several U.S. states $29.5 million to settle a lawsuit alleging it worked with other index-fund managers to pressure coal companies to reduce output.

headline: State Street Investment Management Expands Industry’s First Actively Managed Corporate Target Maturity ETFs Suite
summary: BOSTON, February 26, 2026--State Street Investment Management announced today the launch of five actively managed target maturity high yield corporate bond ETFs. In providing access to high yield bonds with matching maturity years ranging from 2027 to 2031, the newest State Street MyIncome ETFs help simplify the process of building custom bond ladder portfolios.
